# Сценарий 3
#
#
#

Заставка 1 

Mug returned to the cabin agitated. He paced from side to side, waiting for his foster mother to arrive. 

When Ka'ah returned, however, Mug announced to her that he wanted to take the trial. 

The old orcish woman got angry. She had told Mug that the tribe would not accept him, that the orcs hated him, that the ordeal was difficult and dangerous. 

To all objections, Mug's answer was the same: he didn't care. He no longer wished to endure the tyranny of the big orcs. 

Then old Ka'ah sighed and said she was not mistaken in the prophecy. Mug is a cursed creature. But he is cursed because he has the blood of the Khan of the Ogres in his veins. His destiny is to rule. For twenty years she kept it a secret, and finally the prophecy began to come true, and it was time to reveal the truth to Mug. 

Mug frowned. The new truth made him even angrier at the big orcs who were humiliating the ogre heir. His desire to become chief had increased tenfold. 

Ka'ah ordered Mug to go to the mountains at dawn. Her best students would meet him there. They will help Mug pass the trial and become a chief. 

Mug still couldn't sleep. At first light, he headed for the mountains, straight for the sacred cave where the avatar of the Hunting Spirit lived...

